Docs.summary: Extends the DataFormWebPart object with features that are common to the Publishing Web Parts.

remarks.para: The CmsDataFormWebPart object provides a platform for the three Publishing Web Parts: Summary Links, Content By Query, and Table of Contents. You can customize the HTML output of publishing Web Parts by using XSL transformations. Web Parts that inherit from the CmsDataFormWebPart will have the benefit of a cached XSL transformation that increases performance.

MemberSignature.Value: public override void FetchCustomizedXsl (out byte[] customizedXsl, out string hashKey);
.method public hidebysig virtual instance void FetchCustomizedXsl([out] unsigned int8[]& customizedXsl, [out] string& hashKey) cil managed
Public Overrides Sub FetchCustomizedXsl (ByRef customizedXsl As Byte(), ByRef hashKey As String)
public: override void FetchCustomizedXsl([Runtime::InteropServices::Out] cli::array <System::Byte> ^ % customizedXsl, [Runtime::InteropServices::Out] System::String ^ % hashKey);

Docs.param: Compiled XSL that is a delta of the customized XSL and the default XSL, and some protection code
A hash key that uniquely identifies the compiled delta XSL
Docs.summary: Retrieves cached compiled XSL that differs from the default XSL.

remarks.para: In order to keep XSL transforms from taking down the server, if the default XSL has been changedin any way, SharePoint 2013 creates a delta between the original "safe" XSL and the new XSL. The delta, which possibly is unsafe, is compiled with some added code to protect against infinite loops. The FetchCustomizedXsl(System.Byte[]@,System.String@) method enables subclasses of the class to cache the results of the compilation of the delta. If the compiled delta XSL is cached as a method, then the compiled delta XSL is retrieved by the FetchCustomizedXsl(System.Byte[]@,System.String@) method.
